# Deploy-time geo scope — what the PRODUCTION geo substrate is built from.
#
# This is deliberately INDEPENDENT of infra/.region (your local docker-compose dev
# scope). Develop against one state locally, deploy a different state or the whole
# US — without touching your dev config. Read by infra/scripts/provision-geo-host.sh,
# which the kamal-docker wrapper runs after a successful `setup` / `deploy`.
#
#   cp backend/.kamal/geo.env.example backend/.kamal/geo.env   # then edit (gitignored)
#
# Set EXACTLY ONE of GEO_REGION_URL or GEO_COUNTRY. Per-invocation env wins over
# this file, e.g.:  GEO_REGION_URL=…iowa-latest.osm.pbf  bin/kamal-docker deploy
#                   GEO_COUNTRY=us                        bin/kamal-docker setup

# A single Geofabrik extract — a state-sized deploy (fast to build). This file is
# SOURCED as shell, so a multi-word GEO_REGION_LABEL must be quoted (e.g.
# GEO_REGION_LABEL="New York"). The state's bbox is matched from the URL slug, so
# the label is only the human-facing name.
GEO_REGION_URL=https://download.geofabrik.de/north-america/us/iowa-latest.osm.pbf
GEO_REGION_LABEL=Iowa

# …OR a whole-country build via the country registry (large; leave the two lines
# above commented out if you use this):
# GEO_COUNTRY=us
#
# Note: a whole-US (or other country) deploy should also match the app's
# GEOCODER_COUNTRY in config/deploy.yml. States are all within the US, so the
# default GEOCODER_COUNTRY=us already covers any single-US-state deploy.
#
# MAP FRAMING + GEOCODING: a single-state deploy (the GEO_REGION_URL above) makes
# the app frame the map on that whole state and geocode within it — the app never
# opens zoomed out to the entire US. bin/kamal-docker derives the state's bounding
# box from this scope (matching the GEO_REGION_URL slug, or GEO_REGION_LABEL),
# writes it to .kamal/deploy-scope.env, and .kamal/secrets feeds it into the
# backend automatically; no config/deploy.yml edit is needed. A GEO_COUNTRY=us
# deploy frames the whole country instead.

# --- Whole-US on-host build tuning (sourced by provision-geo-host.sh) ---
# Only needed for a GEO_COUNTRY country build; a single state builds fine unset.
# Planetiler OOMs the US tile build at the default JVM heap; size PLANETILER_XMX
# to the box (leave headroom for the OS + other containers — on a 16 GB host use
# ~12g, NOT 16g). GEO_BUILD_JOBS caps build threads.
#   PLANETILER_XMX=12g
#   GEO_BUILD_JOBS=8
# The Nominatim import shm_size + THREADS are set on the geocoder accessory in
# config/deploy.yml (options.shm-size + env THREADS), not here.
